## Remarks

`SKWebpEncoder` encodes single frames and animated sequences to WebP using <xref:SkiaSharp.SKWebpEncoderOptions> to control quality and compression settings.

For single images, use one of the `Encode` overloads. For animated WebP files, use `EncodeAnimated` with a collection of <xref:SkiaSharp.SKWebpEncoderFrame> instances.

## Examples

```csharp
using var bitmap = new SKBitmap(200, 200);
using var pixmap = bitmap.PeekPixels();
using var data = SKWebpEncoder.Encode(pixmap, SKWebpEncoderOptions.Default);
File.WriteAllBytes("output.webp", data.ToArray());
```
